title: [Twin Canyons, Western Canyon]
description: Rising higher and higher, the walls of the canyon leave only a small sliver of the night sky visible overhead.  Falling pebbles create a constant background of echoes that disrupt a continuous chattering noise emanating from cracks in the northeast face of the rock outcrop.  To the south, the steep southern wall of the canyon can be seen as a towering black void against the silver night sky.

Rising higher and higher, the walls of the canyon leave only a small sliver of daylight visible overhead.  Falling pebbles create a constant background of echoes that disrupt a continuous chattering noise emanating from cracks in the northeast face of the rock outcrop.  To the south, the steep southern wall of the canyon can be seen towering several hundred feet into the sky.
paths: Obvious paths: north, east, southeast, northwest
